All satellite units of the Intelligence Response Team and Special Tactical Squad of the Nigerian Police has been closed down.  The Inspector-General of Police, Usman Alkali Baba gave the order on Tuesday. He gave the order hours after the suspended Deputy Commissioner of Police and Head, Intelligence Response Team of the Nigeria Police Force, Abba Kyari, was arrested alongside his accomplices over their alleged involvement in drug trafficking. Channels TV reports that all serving officers in the satellite units have been directed to report to the Force Headquarters, Abuja for debriefing. The Police source disclosed that officers in these units will be demobilized and posted to Commands across the country. Details soon..  Source The Inspector-General of Police, Usman Baba has called for the arrest of NDLEA officers who connived with disgraced cop, Abba Kyari to traffick cocaine. The IGP urged the Chairman of National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, Brig-Gen Buba Marwa (retd), to immediately arrest the officers of the agency involved in the… In "News" Attorney General of the Federation (AGF) and Justice Minister Abubakar Malami (SAN) has advised the police on the fate of embattled former Commander of Police Intelligence Response Team (IRT), Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP) Abba Kyari. Inspector General of Police (IGP) Usman Baba, who announced this yesterday, said the police… In "News" It has been revealed that serious pressure is being heaped on the Nigerian police authorities in order to clear disgraced police officer, Abba Kyari. According to Sahara Reporters, the pressure is coming from top government officials, monarchs and ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftains. They want suspended commander of the… In "News"